## Meal Overview

The fastest complete dinner in the rotation. Stir-fries reward prep — once everything is sliced and sauced, cooking takes under 10 minutes. Snow peas stay crisp-tender, chicken stays juicy, and the sauce coats everything in savory gloss.

## Cooking Strategy

1. **Start rice** - 20 minutes in rice cooker
2. **Prep everything** - slice chicken, trim snow peas, mix sauce
3. **Steam edamame** - 5 minutes, set aside
4. **Stir-fry** - high heat, chicken first, then vegetables, then sauce
5. **Serve** - rice in bowls, stir-fry on top, edamame alongside

## Notes

- Have all ingredients prepped before the wok gets hot
- A wok is ideal but a large skillet works
- Toasted sesame oil drizzled at the end adds depth
